{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":122323,"duration_api_ms":121546,"num_turns":3,"result":"Here's what the scan found — no secrets, migrations, lock files, or generated code exist in this repo, so those categories are clean. The protected files are:\n\n**CI/CD**\n- `.github/workflows/*.yml` — pipeline definitions; broken releases ship silently\n\n**Build infrastructure**\n- `bundle.sh` — packages the distributable; errors produce broken releases\n- `Dockerfile.test` — test environment; changes affect the published GHCR image\n- `Makefile` — developer/CI entrypoint\n\n**Security-critical libraries**\n- `lib/config.sh` — auth checks, budget math, env setup\n- `lib/agent.sh` — budget enforcement, cost tracking, API response validation (runaway spend risk)\n- `lib/validate.sh` — quality gates on all generated artifacts\n\n**Validator scripts**\n- `scripts/validate-skill.sh` / `scripts/validate-subagent.sh` — Phase 5 gatekeepers; weakening rules silently degrades output\n\n**Structural contracts**\n- `schemas/*.json` — agent I/O contracts; schema drift breaks structured output parsing silently\n- `tests/fixtures/**/*.json` — ground-truth test data; hand-editing makes tests lie\n\n**Config**\n- `.claude/settings.json` — hook wiring; hand-edits desync scripts from settings\n- `.gitignore` — removing `.ultrainit/` would commit developer answers to the repo","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"f6a780c1-e176-4119-816b-9a5e87751248","total_cost_usd":0.34976265,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":29768,"cache_read_input_tokens":55361,"output_tokens":2077,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":29768,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":330,"cache_read_input_tokens":28525,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1243,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1243},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":7,"outputTokens":2077,"cacheReadInputTokens":55361,"cacheCreationInputTokens":29768,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.15941429999999998,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":88,"outputTokens":6066,"cacheReadInputTokens":1102041,"cacheCreationInputTokens":39781,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.19034834999999997,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"protected_files":[{"path_pattern":".github/workflows/*.yml","reason":"CI/CD pipeline definitions — incorrect edits can break releases, test runs, or the Docker image publish workflow.","safe_alternative":"Discuss pipeline changes with the team and test in a feature branch before merging to main."},{"path_pattern":"bundle.sh","reason":"Release bundling script that packages ultrainit.sh into the distributable single-file artifact. Errors here silently ship broken releases.","safe_alternative":"Run `make release` (or `make test-all` first) and verify the bundle output manually before pushing a tag."},{"path_pattern":"Dockerfile.test","reason":"Defines the isolated bats-core test environment. Changes affect every CI test run and the published GHCR image.","safe_alternative":"Build and verify locally with `make test-image` before committing. Changes trigger an automatic image rebuild on push to main."},{"path_pattern":"Makefile","reason":"Orchestrates build, test, and release targets. Incorrect changes break the developer workflow and CI.","safe_alternative":"Edit targets carefully; run `make test-all` after any change to verify nothing regressed."},{"path_pattern":".claude/settings.json","reason":"Claude Code settings including hook wiring. Hand-editing can desync hooks from their scripts.","safe_alternative":"Use `ultrainit.sh` to regenerate, or use the Claude Code settings UI. For hook changes, update the hook script and re-run merge logic."},{"path_pattern":"lib/config.sh","reason":"Security-critical: handles dependency checking, Claude auth verification (`claude auth status`), budget arithmetic, and environment setup. Errors here can silently bypass auth or blow the budget.","safe_alternative":"Make changes in a branch, add a corresponding unit test in `tests/unit/config_budget.bats` or `tests/unit/config_workdir.bats`, and run `make test-unit` before merging."},{"path_pattern":"lib/agent.sh","reason":"Security-critical: controls budget enforcement (`--max-budget-usd`), cost tracking, API response validation, and agent spawning. A bug here can cause runaway API spend or accept malformed outputs.","safe_alternative":"Add a test in `tests/unit/agent_run.bats` or `tests/unit/agent_helpers.bats` covering the changed behavior. Run `make test-unit` before merging."},{"path_pattern":"lib/validate.sh","reason":"Enforces quality gates on all generated artifacts (CLAUDE.md length, generic-phrase detection, hook wiring). Weakening checks here silently degrades output quality.","safe_alternative":"Add regression tests in `tests/unit/validate_claude_md.bats` or `tests/unit/validate_hook.bats` before modifying validation rules."},{"path_pattern":"scripts/validate-skill.sh","reason":"Standalone validator that enforces skill frontmatter, file-reference minimums, and generic-phrase bans. Used in Phase 5 and tested independently.","safe_alternative":"Update `tests/scripts/validate_skill.bats` alongside any rule changes and run `make test-scripts` to verify."},{"path_pattern":"scripts/validate-subagent.sh","reason":"Standalone validator for subagent frontmatter and tool scoping. Same risk as validate-skill.sh.","safe_alternative":"Update `tests/scripts/validate_subagent.bats` alongside any rule changes and run `make test-scripts` to verify."},{"path_pattern":"schemas/*.json","reason":"JSON schemas define the contract between orchestrator and every agent. Changing a schema breaks structured output parsing for all agents that use it, potentially silently producing empty findings.","safe_alternative":"When adding fields, add them as optional. Update the corresponding fixture in `tests/fixtures/findings/` and run `make test-all` to catch breakage."},{"path_pattern":"tests/fixtures/**/*.json","reason":"Realistic fixtures that all unit and integration tests depend on. Incorrect edits cause tests to pass against a fantasy that doesn't match real claude output.","safe_alternative":"Capture real `claude -p --output-format json` output to update fixtures. Never hand-craft values — they must match the actual response envelope format."},{"path_pattern":".gitignore","reason":"Controls what gets committed. Accidentally removing `.ultrainit/` would commit intermediate findings (including potentially sensitive developer answers) to the repo.","safe_alternative":"Append new patterns with `echo 'pattern' >> .gitignore` rather than rewriting the file."}]},"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"482b02c1-d781-4b3b-8671-7a90588bc309"}
